PAR MK3 firmware for sd2snes / FX Pak Pro
=========================================
Version: __VERSION__

INSTALL (easy)
--------------
1. Copy the "sd2snes" folder from this archive onto the ROOT of your SD card,
   merging into the existing sd2snes folder (overwrite when prompted).
2. Add the Pro Action Replay MK3 BIOS dump yourself: put "par_mk3.bin" into the
   sd2snes folder (see the placeholder note inside it).
3. Re-insert the card and power on.

WHICH FIRMWARE RUNS?
--------------------
Both ship; the bootloader auto-picks the one for your hardware:
  firmware.im3  ->  sd2snes (MK.III, LPC1768)
  firmware.stm  ->  FX Pak Pro (STM32)

CONTENTS
--------
  sd2snes/firmware.im3      sd2snes MK.III firmware
  sd2snes/firmware.stm      FX Pak Pro firmware
  sd2snes/fpga_parmk3.bi3   PAR MK3 FPGA core
  sd2snes/fpga_mini.bi3     boot/mini FPGA core
  sd2snes/menu.bin          menu ROM (sd2snes)
  sd2snes/m3nu.bin          menu ROM (FX Pak Pro)

BLANK CARD?
-----------
This is the PAR MK3 add-on build. The base support files (fpga_base.bi3, the
DSP/CX4 ROM dumps, etc.) are NOT included. If you start from an empty card,
install an official sd2snes / FX Pak Pro firmware release first, then copy this
archive's sd2snes folder over it.

USAGE
-----
Enable it under  Settings > Pro Action Replay > Enable Pro Action Replay.
Every ROM you launch then boots through the MK3 BIOS (Cheats / Trainer).
Per-game saves land in /sd2snes/saves/ :
  <game>.srm     game battery save
  <game>.mk3srm  MK3 cheat / trainer state
